===Glyph origin===
{{Han etyl}}
{{liushu|p}}: a gate. Compare {{och-l|戶|(one) door}}, which is half of this character ([[𠁣]]).

===Etymology===
From {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*mur||mouth; lip; to hold in mouth; to chew; face; gills}} (STEDT). Cognate with {{cog|bo|མུར་བ||to masticate}}, {{cog|bo|མུར་འགྲམ||jawbone; cheek}}, {{cog|lus|hmûi||lips; upper lip}} and {{och-l|吻|lips; corner of the lips}}.
; “-gate”
: {{semantic loan|zh|en|-gate}}, which is a back-formation from {{m|en|Watergate}}. Also influenced by {{ncog|ja|羅生門}}.

